McDonnell, founder of the Southtown Economist newspaper...TIMELESS TUDOR ELEGANCE on LONGWOOD DRIVE  Behind its distinguished facade, 10162 South Longwood Drive unfolds as a masterwork of Tudor Revival design-romantic, dignified, and rooted in history. Built in 1929, this remarkable residence channels the spirit of a great English country home, where architecture was intentional, materials were chosen to endure, and every detail served both beauty and function.  The home was commissioned by William H. McDonnell, founder of the Southtown Economist newspaper and a prominent civic figure of his time. Its architect, Homer G. Sailor, brought a refined hand to the design, creating a residence that feels both stately and welcoming. In 2021 the home was renovated to blend that formal approach with todays modern amenities | new electrical, plumbing, drain tiles, kitchen, baths, and basement.With four bedrooms and three-and-a-half baths, the interior offers a series of gracious rooms designed for entertaining and comfortable daily life. The home's scale, symmetry, and period craftsmanship create a sense of permanence rarely  found today. Stone | Lead Glass Windows | Moldings  Set along the gently curving route of Longwood Drive, the property enjoys a setting that feels quietly removed from the city - yet it's lovingly known as the "Village in the City". This is a home of substance | history | and enduring presence. Make this home your next chapter. Close to Metra and Shops on 103rd. This home is located in both the Ridge and Longwood Historic Districts. SHOWINGS will be on Sunday, December 14, 2025 | 11am - 6pm.Continue Reading

With 875 feet of water frontage, this six-acre, two-parcel offering along Coecles Harbor comes with architectural plans fully approved by both the Suffolk County Department of Health Services and the Department of Environmental Conservation, clearing the way for your vision to become reality. Conceptual renderings reveal the possibilities: a modern main residence of approximately 6,000 square feet, complemented by a 3,000-square-foot guest house—just one of many configurations available. With two separate parcels, you can build a main home and guest retreat or create two sister residences, each with spectacular water views.The Pandion Subdivision elevates the experience further with exclusive amenities, including a deep water dock, tennis courts, boat storage, and a newly constructed waterfront boathouse perfect for entertaining or unwinding after a day on the water. The setting is extraordinary—surrounded by protected wetlands, preserved land, and panoramic vistas of Coecles Harbor, Mashomack Preserve, Ram Island, and Gardiners Bay beyond.Boating enthusiasts will appreciate the multiple docking options and included harbor mooring, providing effortless access to Sag Harbor, the North Fork, and beyond. Located just five minutes from the Shelter Island South Ferry and only a mile from the center of town, this property combines total seclusion with ultimate convenience.Wake up to endless sunrises, soak in the tranquil views, and build the compound of your dreams.
